      "span_text": "When analyzed by type of alcoholic beverage consumed, users in the highest quantile of beer and liquor, but not wine, were at significantly increased risk for ESCC. Previous studies indicate that wine drinking is a strong risk factor for ESCC  ; however, only 0.3 percent of the subjects (n ¼ 1,462) in our study consumed more than three drinks of wine per day, limiting power."
